title: Electricity prices for households in Denmark 2010 - 2019 , semi-annually
summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Euro cents per kilowatt-hour, with a total of 19 data points. The chart has 7 significant trends.
The longest trend is moderately negative which exists from 2018_S1 to 2016_S1.
Differently, the next significant trend is extremely positive which exists from 2012_S1 to 2010_S1.
Likewise, the next significant trend is slightly negative which exists from 2019_S1 to 2018_S1.
On the contrary, the next significant trend is moderately negative which exists from 2016_S1 to 2015_S1.
Conversely, the next significant trend is moderately negative which exists from 2015_S1 to 2014_S1.
Differently, the next significant trend is moderately negative which exists from 2014_S1 to 2013_S1.
Contrarily, the next significant trend is moderately negative which exists from 2013_S1 to 2012_S1.
gold: Between 2010 and the first half of 2018 , the overall household price for electricity in Denmark increased by approximately 4.53 euro cents per kilowatt-hour to 31.23 euro cents . This was the highest price during this period . Electricity prices per kilowatt-hour were at their lowest in the first half of 2010 at 26.7 euro cents .
